Layer 2 — The Flow Engine

AI models how goods move through the world.

Inputs include:
	•	inventory levels
	•	orders
	•	production capacity
	•	shipping routes
	•	costs
	•	delays
	•	weather
	•	port congestion
	•	geopolitical risk

The AI continuously solves a giant optimization problem.

